            "text": "Numbers 18:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". We find in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Samuel 6:6-7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " an instance of the fatal result of the violation of this command by Uzzah, who being, as is most probable, a Levite, and of the family of Kohath, ought to have been acquainted with the law respecting the removal of the Ark. It is obvious that the Kohathites, as the immediate assistants of the priests, in regard to the vessels of the Sanctuary, were specially exposed to the risk of violating the law by touching the most holy things.",
            "children": []
