  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when Aaron and his sons had made an end of covering the sanctuary,.... Not the holy place, nor the most holy place, for these were not covered by them; but \"the holy things\" in them, as the Septuagint version, the ark, shewbread table, &c. and all \"the vessels of the sanctuary\"; all appertaining to those holy things, which are before mentioned. Jarchi interprets the \"sanctuary\", or the \"holiness\", of the ark and altar: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the vessels of the sanctuary; of the candlestick and the instruments of ministry: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as the camp is to set forward; which made the covering of them necessary, in order to their being carried as that moved: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "after that the sons of Kohath shall come to bear it; or rather them, all the holy things, and their vessels, and that upon their shoulders: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but they shall not touch any holy thing; even in bearing them, neither the ark nor any other, only the staves and bar, on which they were carried: lest they die; by the immediate hand of God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "these things are the burden of the sons of Kohath, in the tabernacle of the congregation; the above things, the ark, &c. which they were to bear on their shoulders, and not make use of wagons to carry them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "these things are the burden of the sons of Kohath, in the tabernacle of the congregation; the above things, the ark, &c. which they were to bear on their shoulders, and not make use of wagons to carry them. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
